This paper is about non-autoregressive neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new training objective for non-autoregressive translation models, which involves calculating the Bag-of-Ngrams (BoN) difference between the model output and the reference sentence. This approach involves optimizing a differentiable objective function, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper may involve neural network architectures and optimization techniques, which could place it under the sub-categories of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) and "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV).
